@baljeet We trained on a box with 4 Pascal Titan X GPU's each with 12GB of RAM and 64GB of host RAM. Each epoch took about 10h55m.

The hyperparameters are described in [run-librivox.sh](https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/issue333/bin/run-librivox.sh). However,  they have yet to be ported to the corresponding file [run-librivox.sh](https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/master/bin/run-librivox.sh) after the refactor. [PS: If you could do so the PR would be more than welcome :-)]

We did a display step and validation step every 5 epochs. However, one should note that early on, epoch 5 and 10 say, the WER report takes a long time to compute as the network then is making lots of spelling errors and the WER calculation is done in the CPU, which is slow. For example I think at epoch 5 the WER report took as long as one epoch. So you may want to do the display step and validation step less often.

