Digging deeper, I find that any Iterator can't be reduced:

```
class CustomObject:
  def __init__(self, a, b):
    self.a = a
    self.b = b
  def __iter__(self):
    return iter((self.a, self.b))
  def __reduce__(self):
    return self.__class__, (self.a, self.b)
  def __next__(self):
    return next(iter(self))
```

