It's a bit confusing, but you should have 2 classes: background and the class of interest.
The array of "non one-hot" target should have shape `(batch_size, 24, 24)` or `(batch_size, 24, 24, 1)`, and array of "one-hot" shape `(batch_size, 24, 24, 2)`:
* `onehot[:, :, :, 0] has value `1` at background pixel positions is and value `0` at class of interest positions; 
* `onehot[:, :, :, 1] has value `0` at background pixel positions `1` at class of interest positions;

You may have a look at #371 - I have added a test for for this loss with one hot encoding `y_true`. You can try to play with the test values of `y_true` and `y_pred` and see what is the loss.

